<span id="freeTextContainer16761340774268557455">This book is clearly written by someone smarter than me, but I couldn&apos;t really get too into the book because of the more complex and lecture-style content that is presented. The writing is eloquent, but it just doesn&apos;t really like to get directly to the point most of the time which frustrated my reading of it. The advice itself sounds good, the style of the writing/content just isn&apos;t my preferred type. Get to the point! I don&apos;t need 2 pages to explain one idea when two sentences will do. That&apos;s </span>
  <span id="freeText16761340774268557455" style="display:none">This book is clearly written by someone smarter than me, but I couldn't really get too into the book because of the more complex and lecture-style content that is presented. The writing is eloquent, but it just doesn't really like to get directly to the point most of the time which frustrated my reading of it. The advice itself sounds good, the style of the writing/content just isn't my preferred type. Get to the point! I don't need 2 pages to explain one idea when two sentences will do. That's just me though. This book is still valuable regardless, it just comes off as meandering and somewhat abstract or feathery throughout the read.</span>
