<div id="review_2924890140" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2924890140" />
    <a title="Bibek" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/89637728-bibek"><img alt="Bibek" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1602503905p2/89637728.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2924890140?book_show_action=true">Sep 03, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bibek" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bibek" href="/user/show/89637728-bibek">Bibek</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2924890140" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17148558435399800253">Unlike many how-to books for writing fiction, John Gardner imparts elitist advice on writing elitist works. From the value of university education to the way techniques in writing can be learned, this book will give you an insight into the creative process, all the while skeptically describing how one can eschew mediocrity and leap into the glorious art of fiction.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


